<item>
            <title>[JDK-8302369] Reduce the stack size of the C1 compiler</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8302369</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>The current fact is that C1 uses more stack space than the C2 compiler, taking method `java.lang.Object::&amp;lt;init&amp;gt;`as an example on the x86_64 platform , the stack size used is 48 bytes for C1 compiler, while only 16 bytes is used for C2 compiler. &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
========== C1-compiled nmethod =====&lt;br/&gt;
0x00007f93311cc747:   push   %rbp &lt;br/&gt;
0x00007f93311cc748:   sub    $0x30,%rsp   // stack sizes is 48 bytes&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
========== C2-compiled nmethod =======&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;pushq   rbp # Save rbp                                                      &lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;subq    rsp, #16    # Create frame    //stack sizes is 16 bytes&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Therefore, the stack space of C1 compiler has great optimization possibilities.</description>
